Currently it is much too easy to accidentally post an internal comment to a customer. i.e. you enter the text first, and then click a button which decides if the comment goes to customer or is internal.

When you click on "Resolve this issue", the form has a much better interface. You first choose whether you are responding to the customer, or making an internal comment using the tabs, then enter message, then click "Resolve this issue". It's a much better and cleaner interface that will prevent accidental internal comments being sent as public comments.

